    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Basicaly, Equip your guys and Wail on all opposition.  The New Sam goes leaps and bounds to help Boromir out, using Sting to remove burdens when he wins.  Concerning hobbits helps out if you have your sites out, as, later in the game, there are bigger minions.  But, Concerning Hobbits is great later in the game, allowing more burdens to be removed.  With Sam out, and the Ring of Rings, Boromir gets Nine resistance.  Scroll of Isildur allows it to boost up to 11.<br />
<br />
The Shadow side uses Forests on the Site path to wreak havok, while there are a few minor combos.<br />
The Witch King is the Big minion. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
